According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Liquefied Petroleum Gas (LPG) Market was valued at USD 162.67 billion in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 214.28 billion by 2032, expanding at a CAGR of 4.1% during the forecast period. The market continues to witness steady growth as governments and industries increasingly adopt LPG as a cleaner and more efficient fuel for residential, commercial, industrial, and transportation applications. Rising demand for clean cooking fuels, expanding petrochemical production, and supportive government initiatives promoting energy accessibility are driving sustained market expansion across both developed and emerging economies.
Liquefied Petroleum Gas, primarily composed of propane and butane, has become one of the world's most versatile energy sources due to its portability, high calorific value, lower carbon emissions compared to coal and traditional fuels, and extensive applications across households, manufacturing, agriculture, and transportation. Increasing urbanization, improving living standards, and growing investments in energy infrastructure continue to strengthen global LPG consumption.
